						<summary>

						<p>KOKKARĀYANPET, TIRUCHCHENGODU TALUK, SALEM DISTRICT.</p>						

						<p>Brahmapurīśvara temple, east wall, left of entrance.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">••• ••• Sarvadhāri, Āḍi 1.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged and unfinished. It is in late characters.</p>						

						<p>It records the grant of some hamlets for the decoration of the God Biramīśvaram-uḍaiya-tambirāṉār in [Mā]taḷipēṭṭai as also the maintenance and repairs of the temple of the said God and for paying the maintenance to a dancemaster <hi rend="italic">naṭṭuvaṉ</hi> (appointed to serve in the temple ?) by Nāgarasaiyyaṉ, the agent of Kiṭṭiṇa-nāyak[kar].</p>						

